comment: Chandler (PHO) sets the screen on Westbrook (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court was upheld and Phoenix is given possession.
Chandler (PHO) makes marginal contact with Roberson (OKC) after attempting to set the screen.
[Observable in enhanced video] Booker (PHO) moves his pivot foot.
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Knight (PHO) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Chandler (PHO) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent, but for less than three seconds.
Knight (PHO) legally contests Westbrook's (OKC) jump shot attempt. Any high-five contact after the release of the shot is considered incidental.
[Detectable with stop watch] Westbrook (OKC) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Knight (PHO) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Chandler (PHO) maintains legal vertical position during Westbrook's attempt to score on the drive to the basket.
Chandler (PHO) and Adams (OKC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court was upheld and Oklahoma City is given possession.
Knight (PHO) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Adams' (OKC) shot attempt.
Chandler (PHO) sets the screen on Roberson (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Chandler (PHO) jumps from point A to point B into Adams (OKC) and affects his shot attempt.
Chandler (PHO) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
